<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 12:31AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Fergus
County through 100 AM MDT...
At 1231 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Grass Range, or 20 miles west of Winnett, moving
northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Grass Range.
This includes the following highways...
Highway 200 between mile markers 111 and 123.
Highway 191 between mile markers 29 and 53.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
